<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1901,2035]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,2010,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,568,2010,2034]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabaricus">
<emphasis box="[329,568,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Barilius malabaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[824,932,2010,2034]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis box="[824,932,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">B. ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its unique colour pattern, consisting of a single or a double row of spots along the length of the body, the first row with 
<number box="[1067,1123,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13</number>
round or oval bluish-green spots 
<number box="[215,257,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales high and 
<number box="[443,484,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales wide and the second row, if present, with 
<number box="[1032,1073,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
smaller spots reaching up to the anal-fin origin (vs. a row of 
<number box="[481,523,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9</number>
large, vertically-elongate, bluish-green blotches 
<number box="[1082,1124,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
scales high and 
<number box="[1318,1360,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
scales wide along the length of the body, of which in large adults the first three blotches are fragmented into a smaller row of blotches: see 
<figureCitation box="[354,438,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1425,1447]" captionTargetBox="[229,1358,628,1398]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[229,1358,628,1399]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Barilius ardens, A, male, unregistered specimen in life, ~ 90 mm SL; B, juvenile unregistered specimen in life, ~ 20.6 mm SL; C, female, paratype, prior to fixation, ZSI / SRC, F. 8813, 85.5 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242893/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">
Figs. 
<number box="[424,438,296,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[488,503,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Barilius malabaricus, A, unregistered specimen in life from aquarium trade ~ 80 mm SL, Kannur, Kerala; B, MKC 416, prior to fixation, 61.8 mm SL, Valapattanam river, Kerala; C, ZSI / SRC, F. 8816, prior to fixation, 76.8 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242898/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">
<number box="[488,503,295,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) Moreover, 
<taxonomicName box="[657,835,296,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabaricus">
<emphasis box="[657,835,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. malabaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1290,296,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis box="[1176,1290,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its fifth ceratobranchial, which has 
<number box="[461,474,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number box="[490,505,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[520,534,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="2.0">2</number>
(vs. 
<number box="[592,605,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number box="[622,637,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[653,666,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="3.0">3</number>
) teeth. 
<taxonomicName box="[752,924,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabaricus">
<emphasis box="[752,924,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. malabaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1235,1387,333,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canarensis">
<emphasis box="[1235,1387,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. canarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,254,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bakeri">
<emphasis box="[151,254,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. bakeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 
<number box="[384,409,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="11.0">11</number>
½ (vs. 
<number box="[490,518,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="10.0">10</number>
½) branched dorsal-fin rays and 
<number box="[890,917,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="14.0">14</number>
½– 
<number box="[954,980,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="15.0">15</number>
½ (vs. 
<number box="[1060,1087,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="13.0">13</number>
½) branched anal-fin rays, and having the dorsal and anal fins margined with bright orange (vs. broadly margined with white: see Figs.4,6 &amp; 
<number box="[1375,1391,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="9.0">9</number>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabaricus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. malabaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can further be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[684,836,440,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canarensis">
<emphasis box="[684,836,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. canarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[892,995,440,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bakeri">
<emphasis box="[892,995,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">B. bakeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having well-defined gill rakers (vs. fleshy, rudimentary gill rakers: see 
<figureCitation box="[546,633,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1262,1284]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,517,1240]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[217,1369,517,1241]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. First gill arch, A, Barilius bakeri, MKC 384, 68.7 mm SL; B, B. canarensis, MKC 415, 63.4 mm SL (Scale bar = 2 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242902/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="403">
Figs. 
<number box="[604,633,476,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="403" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
