<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="404" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,672,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Description.</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation box="[408,507,672,697]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1343,308,1270]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric data of for BarIlIus ardens (n = 6, ZSI / SRC, F. 8812, F. 8813, MKC 385), B. canarensIs (n = 3, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, MKC 415), B. malabarIcus (n = 10, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, F. 8816, MKC 416), B. bakerI (n = 6, MKC 295, 384)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFF48FF16FF2E" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" tableUuid="DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFF48FF16FF2E">
Tables 
<number box="[493,507,673,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
and 
<number box="[572,586,673,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">
<tableCitation box="[572,586,673,697]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,239,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[159,1314,1421,1856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 2. Meristic data of BarIlIus ardens (n = 6, ZSI / SRC, F. 8812, F. 8813, MKC 385), B. canarensIs (n = 3, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, MKC 415), B. malabarIcus (n = 10, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, F. 8816, MKC 416), B. bakerI (n = 6, MKC 295, 384)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFAEAFA83FAB0" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" tableUuid="DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFAEAFA83FAB0">2</tableCitation>
</number>
for morphometric and meristic characters, and 
<figureCitation box="[1153,1265,672,697]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Barilius malabaricus, A, unregistered specimen in life from aquarium trade ~ 80 mm SL, Kannur, Kerala; B, MKC 416, prior to fixation, 61.8 mm SL, Valapattanam river, Kerala; C, ZSI / SRC, F. 8816, prior to fixation, 76.8 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242898/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Figures 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1296,673,696]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,611,633]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,589]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[217,1369,193,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Barilius malabaricus, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, 90.7 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242899/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">7</figureCitation>
for general appearance. Body deep, depth about one-third SL, laterally compressed, dorsal profile slightly curved, ventral profile deeply convex. Caudal peduncle deep, depth almost equal to length. Head small, length about one-fourth SL, depth more than three-fourths length, dorsal profile almost straight, a slightly raised at nape. Eyes large, placed forward, diameter about one-third HL. Mouth oblique, angle of gape reaching middle of orbit. Two pairs of minute barbels (rostral and maxillary). Nostrils closer to eye than to snout tip. Lower jaw slightly longer than upper jaw. Snout length about one-third HL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Dorsal fin with 
<number box="[373,387,925,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
simple and 
<number box="[522,548,924,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="11.0">11</number>
½ (
<number box="[585,614,925,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="10.0">10</number>
) branched rays, posterior margin slightly concave, origin anterior to analfin origin. Pelvic fin short, not reaching anal-fin origin, with 
<number box="[852,866,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
simple and 
<number box="[1007,1021,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[1039,1068,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="10.0">10</number>
) branched rays. Anal fin with 
<number box="[1422,1436,961,985]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
simple and 
<number box="[292,319,996,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="14.0">14</number>
½ (
<number box="[362,376,996,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
)– 
<number box="[401,428,996,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="15.0">15</number>
½ (
<number box="[472,486,997,1021]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays, ventral margin deeply concave, a sharp curve among first few branched rays. Pectoral fin with 
<number box="[542,556,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
simple and 
<number box="[709,736,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="11.0">11</number>
(
<number box="[757,771,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
)– 
<number box="[795,823,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="12.0">12</number>
(
<number box="[845,859,1033,1057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays. Caudal fin deeply forked, lobes subequal, lower lobe slightly longer, with 
<number box="[626,636,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[654,669,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
+ 
<number box="[688,702,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[720,730,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
rays. Lateral line complete, slightly curved with 
<number box="[1285,1313,1068,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="36.0">36</number>
(
<number box="[1330,1346,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
), 
<number box="[1368,1396,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="37.0">37</number>
(
<number box="[1412,1427,1069,1093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
) or 
<number box="[181,209,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="38.0">38</number>
(
<number box="[227,239,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
) + 
<number box="[280,294,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<number box="[310,339,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="10.0">10</number>
) pored scales. Predorsal scales 
<number box="[695,724,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="15.0">15</number>
(
<number box="[734,749,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="6.0">6</number>
), 
<number box="[771,799,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="16.0">16</number>
(
<number box="[814,829,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
) or 
<number box="[877,905,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="17.0">17</number>
(
<number box="[921,937,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
); scales in transverse line on body ½ 
<number box="[1354,1367,1104,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[1384,1400,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="4.0">4</number>
), 
<number box="[1422,1436,1105,1129]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[160,175,1141,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
), ½ 
<number box="[221,234,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[251,265,1141,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
) / 
<number box="[292,301,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[310,324,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
½ (
<number box="[363,377,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
)– 
<number box="[402,415,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[432,446,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
) between dorsal-fin origin and pelvic-fin base, 
<number box="[987,1001,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
½ (
<number box="[1039,1053,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
)– 
<number box="[1078,1091,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[1108,1122,1140,1165]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
) scales between lateral line and anal-fin base. Gill rakers slender, well-defined, 
<number box="[765,779,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<number box="[801,816,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
), 
<number box="[843,857,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[878,893,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
) + 
<number box="[941,955,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[976,991,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.0">3</number>
), 
<number box="[1018,1032,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[1053,1068,1177,1201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
) rakers on first gill arch. Fifth ceratobranchial with 
<number box="[387,400,1212,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number box="[416,431,1212,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[447,461,1212,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.0">2</number>
teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1248,1273]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Coloration.</emphasis>
In life (see 
<figureCitation box="[468,535,1248,1273]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[217,1369,553,1823]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Barilius malabaricus, A, unregistered specimen in life from aquarium trade ~ 80 mm SL, Kannur, Kerala; B, MKC 416, prior to fixation, 61.8 mm SL, Valapattanam river, Kerala; C, ZSI / SRC, F. 8816, prior to fixation, 76.8 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242898/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Fig. 
<number box="[519,535,1248,1273]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
), body bright bluish-silver with one or two rows of spots on flank, first row with 
<number box="[151,221,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13</number>
round or oval bluish-green spots 
<number box="[616,657,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales high and 
<number box="[855,897,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales wide, second row (if present) with 
<number box="[1394,1436,1285,1309]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
smaller spots reaching up to anal-fin origin. Sometimes in large specimens spots of second row further break up into a smaller third row consisting of 
<number box="[575,617,1357,1381]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
minute spots. Dorsal fin and anal fin bases black, fin margins lined with orange sometime mixed with white. Caudal fin black, medial rays and lobe tips white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Preserved specimens (
<figureCitation box="[452,522,1428,1453]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,611,633]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,589]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[217,1369,193,590]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Barilius malabaricus, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, 90.7 mm SL, Payaswini River, Kerala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242899/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
Fig. 
<number box="[507,522,1429,1453]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) lose bright colours: greyish, darker on the dorsal side, progressively becoming lighters towards the abdomen, which is white. The spots on body dark grey. Fins opaque, dorsal, anal and caudal with black bases black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="404" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,672,1633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1536,1561]" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[358,595,1537,1561]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="404" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabaricus">
<emphasis box="[358,595,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="404">Barilius malabaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from the Payaswini and Vallapattanam Rivers, both of which flow through north Kerala, but probably occurs throughout a wider range in the southern Karnataka and northern Kerala regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
